subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Coastal waters and deeper waters of continental shelves and slopes. South African Fur Seals breed on the mainland and islands, and Australian Fur Seals breed on islands in the Bass Strait. Australian Fur Seals favor rocky habitat when ashore. Predators include great white sharks (Carcharodon carcharias) and Killer Whales (Orcinus orca). Jackals (
Canidae
) and hyenas (
Hyaenidae
) are predators at mainland rookeries of South African Fur Seals.
